Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @tomato{1}(diced). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}(roughly chopped). Halve and
peel @onion{1}(halved and peeled); thinly slice one half. Finely chop remaining
onion until you have 2 TBSP. Quarter @lime{1}(quartered). Halve, core, and thinly
slice @green bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and sliced) into strips.

== Tomato Salsa ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, cilantro, chopped onion, juice from half the
lime, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Hot Sauce Crema ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tbsp} with as much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you
like. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.
Season with salt.

== Beef Mixture ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
@ground turkey{10%oz}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, @chili powder{1%tsp}, and
a few big pinches of salt. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned,
~{4-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Once beef is browned, add bell pepper, sliced onion, and a pinch of salt to pan.
Cook, stirring, until veggies are tender and beef is cooked through,
~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @beef stock concentrate{1} and 1/4 cup water (1/2 cup water for 4 servings).
Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt; remove pan from heat and
set aside.

== Tostadas ==

Drizzle @flour tortillas{6} with 1 TBSP olive oil (2 TBSP for 4 servings); brush or
rub to coat all over. Arrange on a #baking sheet{} in a single layer (divide
between two sheets for 4). Gently prick each tortilla in a few places with a
#fork{}.

Bake on top rack, flipping halfway through, until lightly golden,
~{4-5%minutes} per side.

> For 4 servings, bake on top and middle racks; flip tortillas and swap rack
> positions halfway through baking.

> Watch carefully—tortillas brown fast!

== Assembly ==

Divide tortillas between #plates{}; evenly sprinkle with
@Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Top with beef mixture, salsa, and crema. Serve
with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Ground Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.